rranean, to join the American squadron in the sea. Fatal Explosion of fire damp.–Friday morning a blast took place at the Plain pit, Rainton, Durham, belonging to the Tempest family, by which between 20 and 30 men and boys were killed. According to report it was caused by the folly of one of the men in using a candle instead of Sir HUMPHREY DAVY's Lamp. Fortunately few of the men had descended to their work, or 160 might have been involved in the calamity. It is supposed the pit would have been wrought out in about a fortnight. The Ordnance reductions have not yet reached Scarborough Castle, of which renowned fortress the Earl of MULGRAVE is Governor. The principal Apothecary of the town, who has a leading influence among the voters of that independent Borough, still continues in the office of Ordnance Store-keeper ; and he very happily displays the emblem of both his profession and his place, by a large mortar in front of his shop. 
