he Union Hotel, the Honourable Baron Sir Peter Murray, and Hon. Miss Murrays; John Bloomfield, Esq. Arrivals–Lord Chief Baron Sir Samuel Shepherd, K.B.; Co-lonel Hasting. The Mid-Lothian fox-hounds meet this day at Long Niddry Dean; and on Saturday at Whittingham. The Pitt Club of Scotland, at a meeting held on Friday, voted two hundred guineas from their funds towards the erection of the monument, proposed to be raised to the memory of their late high-ly respected President the Earl of Hopetoun. Individual sub-scriptions were also made at the same time by various members of the Club. Yesterday the quartern loaf rose one penny, it is now selling at 10d., and in the suburbs of the city at 9d. His Royal Highness the Duke of York has been graciously pleased to appoint Dr Theodore Gordon Physician Extraordinary to his household. On Monday evening a thief contrived to cut out a pane of glass from a shop window in the terrace, and to carry off a quantity of oranges. The shopkeeper, who was in the back shop, heard a scraping noise, and on stepping out to the door he saw the thief making off with his booty. We are happy to learn that Wilsontown Iron Works are to be a-gain set agoing in the spring; and that the now almost deserted vil-lage will be again enlivened with inhabitants and business. On Sunday night a fine boy, about four years of age, in his father's house in the Lawnmarket, having gone too near the grate, the fire caught hold of his pinafore, which instantly communicated to his clothes and set them in a blaze. Notwithstanding all the exertions of his father to extinguish the flames, and who, by that means, was much burnt in the hands, the child was so severely scorched that he lingered in great agony till Monday morning, when he died.",article,51.png
